# Frontend Rules (Shimizu Technology Design Guide)

## HARD RULES (NON-NEGOTIABLE)
- NO EMOJI in UI — use Lucide React icons ONLY
- Brand tokens via CSS custom properties — no hardcoded colors
- Mobile-first responsive design
- 44px minimum touch targets for all interactive elements

## Tech Stack
- React 18 with TypeScript
- Vite for bundling
- Tailwind CSS v4 for styling
- Framer Motion for animations
- Lucide React for icons

## Styling
- Use CSS custom properties for all colors (defined in index.css)
- Access via `style={{ color: 'var(--color-text-primary)' }}`
- Dark mode uses `.dark` class on `<html>` element
- Follow 8px grid for spacing
- Max content width: `max-w-5xl` (1024px)

## Animation
- Use Framer Motion for all animations
- Standard easing: `[0.22, 1, 0.36, 1]` (dramatic ease-out)
- Duration: 200-300ms for micro-interactions, 500-800ms for reveals
- Stagger children with 0.08s delay between items
- Always wrap animated presence in `<AnimatePresence>`

## Components
- One component per file
- Props interface defined above the component
- JSDoc comments explaining purpose
- Use custom hooks for shared logic (hooks/ directory)

## API Integration
- All API calls in `lib/api.ts`
- Typed request/response interfaces
- Handle loading, error, and success states
- Use polling hook for async status checks
